	He said Castilla, despite his phenomenal batting statistics,  
isn't as big of a star in Colorado as some other players. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's huge here. There, it's not even close,'' he said. ``He  
might be the most underrated player in baseball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Teammate Dante Bichette, no stranger to fame himself, said  
Castilla seemed to be holding up well. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's not too much the nervous type,'' he said. ``It's a lot of  
fun. I couldn't wait to get here and see the reception he's 
getting.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Manager Jim Leyland said he welcomed the attention Castilla was  
getting but hoped it wouldn't detract from the game itself. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want Vinny to have his day and all, but we also have to  
realize this is a real game,'' he said. 
</P>
