<HEADLINE> Commitisize Wins El Rincon Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Commitisize led the entire way to win  
Sunday's $150,000 El Rincon Handicap by 1 1/4 lengths over Majorien. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the 15th stakes triumph at the Santa Anita  
winter-spring meeting for trainer Bob Baffert, breaking the record 
of 14 he shared with Neil Drysdale (1997-98) and Charlie 
Whittingham (1970-71). 
</P>
<P>
	It came a day after the Baffert-trained pair of General  
Challenge and Prime Timber finished 1-2 in the $750,000 Santa Anita 
Derby. The Santa Anita meeting finishes April 19. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by David Flores and carrying 117 pounds, Commitisize  
covered 1 1/8 miles on turf in 1:48 1-5 and paid $8.20, $4.80 and 
2.80. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the sixth in 16 lifetime starts for Commitisize and  
was worth $90,000, raising the career earnings of the 4-year-old 
son of Explodent to $538,242. 
</P>
<P>
	``This horse is a pro and he knows what he's doing,'' Flores  
said. ``When I picked up the reins the last part of the race, he 
really picked it up and finished so well.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Majorien, the 2-1 second-favorite ridden by Kent Desormeaux and  
carrying 117 pounds, crossed the finish line 1 1/4 lengths ahead of 
Ladies Din and returned $3.40 and $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din paid $2.20 to show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
