<HEADLINE> Four Shot To Death in Mich. Eatery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Three barbecue restaurant employees and a child  
were found fatally shot Sunday in the eatery, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers called to the Prestige Restaurant about 7:30 a.m. found  
the victims ``throughout'' the restaurant, said police spokesman 
Officer Octaveious Miles. He had no details about how police were 
called. 
</P>
<P>
	Details were still sketchy Sunday afternoon. Police didn't know  
the child's age or possible connection to the other victims, the 
time of the shootings or a definite motive. No arrests had been 
made. 
</P>
<P>
	Detroit television station WJBK reported Sunday that the youth  
was 12. 
</P>
<P>
	The restaurant closed around midnight, and Miles said  
investigators think the shootings happened sometime between then 
and when the bodies were found. He refused to release details about 
where the bodies were. 
</P>
<P>
	``They're still going through a lot of evidence out there,''  
Miles said. 
</P>
