<HEADLINE> Yankees Place Pettitte on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Andy Pettitte, who has won 55 games for the  
New York Yankees in the last three seasons, has been placed on the 
15-day disabled list retroactive to March 26. 
</P>
<P>
	The 26-year-old left-hander, who has been bothered by a sore  
elbow, isn't expected to miss more than one or two starts. Pettitte 
was 16-11 last year with a 4.24 ERA. 
</P>
