on the 15-day disabled list retroactive to March 26; optioned 
right-handers Ryan Bradley, Jay Tessmer and Ben Ford to Triple-A 
Columbus, and purchased the contracts of infielder Clay Bellinger 
and right-hander Jason Grimsley. 
</P>
<P>
	Bradley started the Yankees' final exhibition game against the  
Los Angeles Dodgers on Sunday and was ineffective, allowing four 
hits and five runs in one-third of an inning. 
