<HEADLINE> DaimlerChrysler May Spin Off Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- DaimlerChrysler AG is considering  
spinning off its financial services unit Debis and making it an 
independent company to be listed on the stock exchange, a newspaper 
reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Welt am Sonntag, quoting anonymous sources, said  
DaimlerChrysler finds Debis business too different from the rest of 
the group, which includes cars, trucks, aerospace and high-tech 
rail systems. 
</P>
<P>
	Company officials could not be reached for comment.  
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this year, the group merged the financial services  
operations of the former Daimler-Benz and Chrysler companies under 
the roof of Berlin-based Debis. 

</P>
