<HEADLINE> Japan Unemployment May Climb Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan, which is already suffering from record-high  
unemployment, may see its jobless rate rise even further to 5.2 
percent, Japan's chief economic planner said Sunday, according to a 
news report. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, the government announced that unemployment in Japan  
had jumped 0.2 percent in February to an unprecedented 4.6 percent, 
dampening hopes for an imminent economic recovery. 
</P>
<P>
	On Sunday, Taichi Sakaiya, the head of Japan's Economic Planning  
Agency, said the worst was yet to come in the employment situation. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is a possibility of the rate going as high as 5.2  
percent,'' Sakaiya was quoted as saying by Kyodo News Agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
