<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Football Great Namath Wants Divorce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Hall of Fame quarterback Joe Namath  
has filed for divorce. 
</P>
<P>
	Namath and his 37-year-old wife Tatiana married in 1984 and have  
a home in Jupiter. They have two children, Olivia, 13, and Jessica, 
8. 
</P>
<P>
	According to court records, Tatiana Namath is not contesting the  
divorce, the Sun-Sentinel reported Sunday. Namath's lawyer, James 
Fox Miller, filed the papers in Broward County circuit court March 
19. 
</P>
<P>
	Namath, 55, remains one of the most celebrated football figures,  
even in retirement. During his years with the New York Jets, 
Namath's playboy image as ``Broadway Joe'' shook the staid NFL. But 
for many years now he has reveled in his life as a doting family 
man. 
</P>
<P>
	Namath was inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame in 1985  
after a 13-year career, 12 with the Jets and the last one with the 
Los Angeles Rams. 
</P>
<P>
	He is best remembered for his guarantee that the Jets, a 17  
1-2-point underdog, would beat the Baltimore Colts in Super Bowl 
III. The Jets won 16-7, a victory that vindicated the upstart AFL. 
</P>
</TEXT>
